 Job Description and Requirements 
 The applicant for an Applications Engineer (AE) on the customer support team should have skills in the use of advanced photonic design tools (Synopsys preferred). You should have a passion for photonic design and modeling and have an interest in helping engineers maximize the capabilities of Synopsys tools. You'll help resolve their most challenging and complex problems. You must have an interest in product development, and be able to understand photonic engineering issues associated with new and advancing technology applications. 
 
 Responsibilities: 
Support photonic customers with complex technical questions, efficiently understanding, diagnosing, troubleshooting, and resolving issues in a customer environment 
Provide technical insight and direction to improve usability, applicability, and adoption of products, platforms, and solutions to meet customer business needs 
Develop and utilize technical material in a variety of ways, including at training sessions, webinars, customer visits, and user group meetings 
Partner with sales and technical leaders to identify business challenges, develop effective solutions, and increase retention of products. 
Qualifications: 
3+ years of experience in integrated optics, photonics, photonic integrated circuits, or physics 
Master/Ph.D. degree in a technical discipline (Optics, Photonics Engineering, Physics, or Mathematics) 
Ability to work on multiple concurrent projects and ability to work well in a team 
Exceptional problem solving, troubleshooting, and organizational skills 
Ability to understand customer requirements and expectations of a commercial software package 
Willingness for international and domestic travel to support customer visits and other events 
Excellent written and verbal skills with the ability to clearly communicate highly technical information 
